{"type":"message","id":"122e7e24","parentId":"2cb3f218","timestamp":"2026-07-13T02:43:38.986Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_8d20dac2d05a470ebd3ce99b","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"mkdir -p /data/workspace/social/linkedin/264468965/posts\n\ncat > /data/workspace/social/linkedin/264468965/posts/2026-07-13-memory-hardware-wall.md << 'EOF'\n---\ntitle: Your AI infrastructure plan just hit a hardware wall\ndate: 2026-07-13T02:43:00Z\npost_url: https://www.linkedin.com/feed/update/urn:li:share:7482263416552939520/\nimage: /data/workspace/social/linkedin/264468965/images/boring-agents-1783699220.png\nchars: 1103\nhashtags:\n  - AI\n  - Infrastructure\n  - Hardware\n  - DataCenter\n  - CloudComputing\n---\n\n𝗬𝗼𝘂𝗿 𝗔𝗜 𝗶𝗻𝗳𝗿𝗮𝘀𝘁𝗿𝘂𝗰𝘁𝘂𝗿𝗲 𝗽𝗹𝗮𝗻 𝗷𝘂𝘀𝘁 𝗵𝗶𝘁 𝗮 𝗵𝗮𝗿𝗱𝘄𝗮𝗿𝗲 𝘄𝗮𝗹𝗹.\n\nDRAM and NAND flash are sold out through 2027. Samsung and SK hynix are dropping $518B on new fabs — but capacity won't come online until late 2027 or 2028.\n\nMicron is meeting only 50-67% of customer demand right now. Sandisk/Kioxia just announced their 10th gen NAND with 332 layers — but that takes time to scale.\n\nThe bottleneck isn't compute. It's memory. And it's going to get worse before it gets better.\n\nThree moves for anyone building AI infrastructure:\n1. Lock in memory supply contracts now — spot prices will keep climbing\n2. Optimize inference efficiency — you won't be able to brute-force your way through\n3. Consider model distillation — smaller models need less memory\n\nThe cloud providers are fighting for the same chips you are. The ones with memory secured win.\n\nWhen's the last time you checked your memory allocation strategy?\n\n#AI #Infrastructure #Hardware #DataCenter #CloudComputing\n\n---\n## Performance (update after 24-48h)\n- Views: \n- Likes: \n- Comments: \n- Shares: \nEOF\n\necho \"Post record saved\""},"partialArgs":"{\"command\": \"mkdir -p /data/workspace/social/linkedin/264468965/posts\\n\\ncat > /data/workspace/social/linkedin/264468965/posts/2026-07-13-memory-hardware-wall.md << 'EOF'\\n---\\ntitle: Your AI infrastructure plan just hit a hardware wall\\ndate: 2026-07-13T02:43:00Z\\npost_url: https://www.linkedin.com/feed/update/urn:li:share:7482263416552939520/\\nimage: /data/workspace/social/linkedin/264468965/images/boring-agents-1783699220.png\\nchars: 1103\\nhashtags:\\n  - AI\\n  - Infrastructure\\n  - Hardware\\n  - DataCenter\\n  - CloudComputing\\n---\\n\\n𝗬𝗼𝘂𝗿 𝗔𝗜 𝗶𝗻𝗳𝗿𝗮𝘀𝘁𝗿𝘂𝗰𝘁𝘂𝗿𝗲 𝗽𝗹𝗮𝗻 𝗷𝘂𝘀𝘁 𝗵𝗶𝘁 𝗮 𝗵𝗮𝗿𝗱𝘄𝗮𝗿𝗲 𝘄𝗮𝗹𝗹.\\n\\nDRAM and NAND flash are sold out through 2027. Samsung and SK hynix are dropping $518B on new fabs — but capacity won't come online until late 2027 or 2028.\\n\\nMicron is meeting only 50-67% of customer demand right now. Sandisk/Kioxia just announced their 10th gen NAND with 332 layers — but that takes time to scale.\\n\\nThe bottleneck isn't compute. It's memory. And it's going to get worse before it gets better.\\n\\nThree moves for anyone building AI infrastructure:\\n1. Lock in memory supply contracts now — spot prices will keep climbing\\n2. Optimize inference efficiency — you won't be able to brute-force your way through\\n3. Consider model distillation — smaller models need less memory\\n\\nThe cloud providers are fighting for the same chips you are. The ones with memory secured win.\\n\\nWhen's the last time you checked your memory allocation strategy?\\n\\n#AI #Infrastructure #Hardware #DataCenter #CloudComputing\\n\\n---\\n## Performance (update after 24-48h)\\n- Views: \\n- Likes: \\n- Comments: \\n- Shares: \\nEOF\\n\\necho \\\"Post record saved\\\"\"}"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"litellm","model":"vertex_ai/zai-org/glm-5-maas","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1783910612794,"responseId":"1VBUav2ZHJfh-eQPyMvF8AM"}}
